You currently have:

```js
const sequelize = new Sequelize(process.env.DATABASE_URL{
```

It is missing a comma after `process.env.DATABASE_URL`.

Change it to:

```js
const sequelize = new Sequelize(process.env.DATABASE_URL, {
```

Full corrected file:

```js
import { Sequelize } from "sequelize";

if (!process.env.DATABASE_URL) {
  throw new Error("ENV MISSING db");
}

const sequelize = new Sequelize(process.env.DATABASE_URL, {
  dialect: "postgres",
  logging: false,
  dialectOptions: {
    ssl: {
      require: true,
      rejectUnauthorized: false,
    },
  },
});

export default sequelize;
```

After fixing that, your next goal is:

```text
Test if app.js can connect to Neon.
```

In [app.js](/Users/anbschool0018/Desktop/Project/00.SCHOOL/00.SchoolProject/Repo/test/app.js:1), add this import near the top:

```js
import sequelize from './config/database.js';
```

